The paper deals with algebraic properties of connectors in component-based systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the expressiveness of stateful connectors, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper explores the use of Petri nets, which is a topic in distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
